                        <p></p>
                        <p>I am a graduate student at the University of California at Irvine. I have the honor of being a part of the <a href="http://vision.ics.uci.edu/">UCI Computational Vision Lab</a> where I am advised by <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~dramanan/">Deva Ramanan</a>. My interests include computer vision, machine learning and computer graphics. I am currently working on connecting 3D object recognition and reconstruction. </p>
                        <p>I recieved my BS in Mathematical Sciences from the <a href="http://sharif.ir/">Sharif University of Technology</a>, Tehran, Iran, in 2010. I had the opportunity to be advised by Mehrdad Shahshahani at IPM Computer Vision group from 2007 until 2010. I was also fortunate enough to work under the supervision of <a href="http://sharif.edu/~daneshgar/">Amir Daneshgar</a>. I have visited the <a href="http://www.nada.kth.se/cvap/">Computer Vision and Active Perception Laboratory (CVAP)</a> at <a href="http://www.kth.se/">KTH University</a> in 2008 where I worked under the supervision of Jan-Olof Eklundh. I have also collaborated with <a href="http://luthuli.cs.uiuc.edu/~daf/">David Forsyth</a> and <a href="http://homes.cs.washington.edu/~ali/">Ali Farhadi</a> on natural language image description in 2010.</p>
